1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,240
Hey, wait.

2
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:45,400
The stitches cost 5,000 baht.
How can I just leave you?

3
00:02:45,480 --> 00:02:47,560
Here. Take it all.

4
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,920
You're giving me all of this?

5
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,480
<i>Are you running away from home?</i>

6
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:56,120
You're really going to give up
your rich life?

7
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:59,040
How do you know I'm rich?

8
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,920
Don't wanna do it? Then go use your card
to withdraw cash and pay me back.

9
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,440
You greedy girl.
Bloodsucker. Just you wait.

10
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:10,920
I've got plenty of enemies,
hundreds, thousands who'd want me dead.

11
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,640
Why does a pretty girl like you
have to work this hard?

12
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:14,560
Is that a compliment?

13
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:17,120
Look who's getting flustered.

14
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,920
I'm your son, and Trai is my brother.

15
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,200
You're not my real son.

16
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:24,640
Rent, food, living expenses,
taking care of you, everything.

17
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:25,640
If you're taking care of me,

18
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:28,400
then you have to provide service
according to my standards only.

19
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:34,720
I drank this stuff just to be polite.

20
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:37,760
What I actually drink is mineral water.

21
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:55,680
No pork and vegetables? I'm not eating it.

22
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:17,399
Whoa, that hurts.

23
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:22,320
If I sleep like this every day,
I'll need a physical therapist.

24
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:24,440
It's too high. Get a new one.

25
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:36,760
Too low.

26
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:38,000
Huh?

27
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:55,160
It's close but not quite.
It's just not right.

28
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:58,080
- It's…
- Ugh!

29
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:04,680
Didn't you say
you wanted to live independently?

30
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,240
Then why are you so damn picky?

31
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:10,960
You're yelling now?
Then give me my wages back.

32
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:12,960
It's all gone.

33
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:15,680
Mineral water, noodles, pillows,

34
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:17,880
plus a 10% service fee.

35
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:18,920
All gone!

36
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:21,480
- All gone?
- Yeah.

37
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,880
Hey, let's talk.

38
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:27,440
Talk? Talk about what?

39
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:30,920
Huh? What's there to talk about?!

40
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,320
- Hey, it hurts!
- Hey! Ow!

41
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,000
You're stingy!

42
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:36,640
You're stingy!

43
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,640
Trai!

44
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,600
Trai!

45
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:08,680
- Let go!
- Stop. Enough. I'm tired.

46
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:12,760
This is what you get for keeping my money
and your friends' money to yourself.

47
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:16,600
If you don't know anything, don't talk!

48
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:18,840
Pakbung, you're still young.
You can change.

49
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:22,080
Lying to people, taking advantage of them,
it's not nice at all.

50
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,800
Hug fee, 3,000.

51
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:31,440
Huh?

52
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:35,720
Hey!

53
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:45,880
After deductions, you still owe me 10,000.

54
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:47,320
Huh?

55
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:52,280
And clean the room.

56
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:54,360
Clean everything.

57
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:57,520
If you don't, I'll charge another 5,000.

58
00:06:58,160 --> 00:06:59,040
5,000?

59
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,160
Yeah.

60
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:03,360
Pakbung. Pakbung!

61
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,360
She's vicious.

62
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:15,800
So the watch is fake.

63
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:19,040
Were your feelings fake too, Darin?

64
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:29,440
Did you really choose my father for money?

65
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:39,280
Pakbung. Pakbung, are you home?

66
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,520
I'm gonna faint.

67
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:59,280
Pakbung! Pakbung!

68
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:04,320
- She's not here.
- Not here?

69
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:07,080
Then who are you? Her husband?

70
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:09,200
Whoa, Uncle, don't curse me like that.

71
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:10,760
I…

72
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:18,000
And who are you? Her father?

73
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:20,880
Father, my ass. Say that again
and I'll slap that mouth of yours.

74
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:23,560
I'm not her father.
I'm here to collect money.

75
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,720
Collect money? From Pakbung?

76
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:28,640
Yeah. Hundreds of thousands.

77
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:32,799
Hey. Tell her

78
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:36,640
that Mr. Song, someone she once respected,

79
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:39,760
someone who lent her money
when she was desperate, was here.

80
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:41,720
But now,

81
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:45,400
I'm struggling too, honestly.

82
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:47,240
I've got to eat, got to live.

83
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:52,200
Tell her to have some pity on me.
I just want my money back.

84
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:58,280
Don't hurt an old man.
I'm tired. I just can't.

85
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,000
Do you have an inhaler?

86
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:13,960
You're so prepared, huh?

87
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,640
Pakbung…

88
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:22,560
Hey.

89
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:23,960
‪HOUSEHOLD EXPENSE - RENT

90
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,800
WATER - ELECTRICITY

91
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:31,000
KANAH'S TUITION

92
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,840
Kanah's tuition.

93
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,320
This is not good.

94
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:38,200
Where did it go?

95
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:41,760
Did you see my money?

96
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:45,120
I kept it right here.
I need it for Kanah's tuition.

97
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:47,760
Your money? I didn't see that.

98
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:49,440
I only saw someone else's money.

99
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:51,720
Did you take my money?

100
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,560
Who do you owe money to?

101
00:09:57,880 --> 00:10:00,440
Debt is the worst suffering
in the world, you know.

102
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:03,040
You borrow money, then you return it.

103
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:06,080
You can't live comfortably
on someone else's pain.

104
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:07,720
Especially old people. disabled people.

105
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:11,000
Old and disabled?

106
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:15,800
Mr. Song?!

107
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:19,200
You gave my money to Mr. Song?

108
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:21,960
Yeah. How much do you owe him?

109
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:26,680
You're a rich heir,
but you got scammed this easily?!

110
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:32,000
You're one step away
from living with Iang.

111
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:35,600
Who's Iang?

112
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:37,000
A buffalo!

113
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:41,200
Hey, Pakbung!

114
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:42,320
MR. SONG

115
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:44,120
- Here you go.
- Yeah.

116
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:51,080
Mr. Song!

117
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:52,320
Give me my money back.

118
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,520
You owe me, Pakbung.

119
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:00,720
I don't. My father does.

120
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:04,920
The new law says debt is inheritance.

121
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:07,280
Your dad owed me, so you pay it back.

122
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:11,040
I let you pay in installments out of pity.

123
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:15,120
And yesterday,
your dad was driving a luxury car.

124
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,160
Where did you see him?

125
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,040
Don't know. I was told.

126
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:24,200
But I heard he married a rich woman.

127
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:26,840
He's rich now.

128
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:29,120
If he has money, tell him to pay me back.

129
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:32,800
He's abandoned me for ten years already.

130
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:34,520
He's never contacted me once.

131
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:38,680
I earned that money myself. It's mine.

132
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:40,080
Give it back.

133
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:41,600
Give it back.

134
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:43,600
- Hey! Hey!
- Pakbung.

135
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:47,640
Pakbung, stop.

136
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,640
Hey.

137
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:53,920
This isn't even half
of what your dad has to pay.

138
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:56,640
Get out, Pakbung. Get out.

139
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:59,400
- Deal with her.
- Don't you understand?

140
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:00,680
- Go!
- Yeah.

141
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:02,840
Deal with her.

142
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,120
Hey.

143
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,080
Hey, help me.

144
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:24,280
Help me!

145
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:27,240
Hey, come help.

146
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,160
Hey, right here.

147
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:36,080
Get in there.

148
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:48,960
Hey! Everything's ruined!

149
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:50,800
Go get them.

150
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:52,080
- Get them.
- Pakbung, let's go.

151
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:54,200
- Now.
- Let's go.

152
00:12:54,280 --> 00:12:57,120
It's a mess. Hey.

153
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:02,120
They're gone. Call the police!

154
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:04,480
Go after them! Go!

155
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:07,160
Call the chief of police. I know him.

156
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:17,280
You okay?

157
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:26,040
Why did you drag me away?

158
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:28,520
I almost got my money back.

159
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:31,160
Do you really think money
is more important than your life?

160
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:33,600
He wouldn't kill me.

161
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:35,080
Then why didn't you go to the police?

162
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:37,360
Loan sharks are illegal, you know.

163
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:39,440
Up to five years in prison.

164
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:42,680
Oh, please. Before he goes to jail,

165
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:44,320
I'd have to sue him, right?

166
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:47,680
Then fight it out in court.
And there are so many courts.

167
00:13:48,280 --> 00:13:50,000
Civil Court, Appeals Court, Supreme Court.

168
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:53,000
How many years do you think
that takes before it finishes?

169
00:13:54,680 --> 00:13:56,840
Then why not film it
and send it to the media?

170
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:59,000
You think I've never tried?

171
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:02,160
The media shows up for a while,
then they're gone.

172
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:04,560
Who's left to deal with it?

173
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:06,040
Me and my brother.

174
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:09,560
Back then, I paid because I was scared.

175
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:13,080
But it never ended.
The interest grew way past the principal.

176
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:16,280
So later, I stopped paying.
If I could run, I ran.

177
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:19,520
If I didn't see him, I didn't pay.
That's how I survived.

178
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:22,920
But today, some white knight

179
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,160
took all my savings
and handed them straight to Mr. Song.

180
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:28,840
There goes

181
00:14:28,920 --> 00:14:31,040
Kanah's tuition!

182
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:36,520
I'm sorry… sorry
about the money and about your father too.

183
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:39,720
I'll find a way to earn it back.

184
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:45,680
Does it hurt?

185
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:49,040
- Just a bit.
- Let me see.

186
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:26,080
You took my money
and dragged me into more trouble.

187
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:29,640
What was it again? Debt

188
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:32,040
is the greatest suffering
in the world, right?

189
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,360
You're in debt to me.

190
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:40,320
Pay it all back.

191
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:10,840
PORRAK POLYCLINIC

192
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:15,800
OPERATING HOURS: MONDAY - SUNDAY
10:00 - 20:00

193
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:17,120
Lock it up.

194
00:16:19,680 --> 00:16:22,040
Excuse me.

195
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:23,440
Have you seen this person?

196
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,800
My friend went missing.

197
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:31,360
His last known location was around here.

198
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:40,040
I'm not sure.
We've had a lot of patients lately.

199
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:43,400
Alright.

200
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:47,920
If you see him, could you contact me?
This is my card.

201
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:53,240
If you provide any information,
there's a reward of 100,000 baht.

202
00:16:53,920 --> 00:16:54,760
Please.

203
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:03,560
Still no news about Trai? Huh?

204
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:06,000
Then send more people.

205
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:07,880
Pay them more.

206
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:13,040
How are they even working?

207
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:17,920
I saw your office light on,
so I came to check.

208
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,040
Are you in a meeting?

209
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:21,800
No,

210
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:24,560
but Pornchai's project is a total mess.

211
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:28,400
You want me to handle it?
So you don't have to work so hard.

212
00:17:29,280 --> 00:17:30,640
Why aren't you home yet?

213
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:34,120
I've got an app project

214
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,400
launching next month.

215
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:37,400
There's a lot to review.

216
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,640
Take care of your health too.

217
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:46,840
I'd die to make Be Rich
number one in the market.

218
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:56,120
If only Trai was half as capable as you.

219
00:17:57,680 --> 00:17:59,640
Only half, would that really be enough?

220
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:06,000
I'm willing to take care of Trai's work.

221
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:09,120
I mean,

222
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:13,040
I'm willing to work on his tasks for you.

223
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:15,920
And I'm willing to take care of you
for the rest of my life.

224
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:28,480
Dad, if Trai never liked your business
and loves his freedom so much,

225
00:18:28,560 --> 00:18:30,320
why don't you just let him go?

226
00:18:33,360 --> 00:18:34,600
Let him go where?

227
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:38,200
He's my son. He has to come back here.

228
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:44,560
Anything else?

229
00:18:55,120 --> 00:18:56,560
It's me!

230
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:58,440
You almost became wet garbage.

231
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:03,320
You know who I am, right?

232
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:09,400
Earlier, you said I'm a rich heir.

233
00:19:09,480 --> 00:19:11,560
But I'm sure that I never told anyone.

234
00:19:11,640 --> 00:19:13,360
How did you know? Google?

235
00:19:16,640 --> 00:19:17,840
I was working at your dad's wedding.

236
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,800
I saw everything, every scene.

237
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:26,440
Oh, that's why.

238
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:29,760
You saved my life
so you could demand a reward, right?

239
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:36,640
Hey. You've got the order a bit wrong.

240
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:39,680
I helped because anyone would help.

241
00:19:39,760 --> 00:19:41,760
But once I knew whose son you were,

242
00:19:42,480 --> 00:19:44,040
- then I…
- Got greedy.

243
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:48,960
Well.

244
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:53,000
A few hundred thousand
from a billionaire's son?

245
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:55,000
That's fair.

246
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:59,200
Someone like you surely has money to burn.

247
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:02,200
Let me make this clear.
I'm not going back home.

248
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:05,000
So that life-saving reward you want,

249
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:06,800
I don't have it.

250
00:20:24,280 --> 00:20:25,960
So how are you gonna live with no money?

251
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:27,200
I'll manage.

252
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:29,760
- No way.
- I will.

253
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:31,720
You've never been poor, have you?

254
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:34,160
From far away,

255
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:36,680
it looks pretty, fascinating even.

256
00:20:36,760 --> 00:20:40,360
But living on salt and rice
is not romantic, okay?

257
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:46,040
You'll have kidney failure and not even
have any money to get treated.

258
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:50,560
Dad might send someone to hurt me.

259
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,520
Huh?

260
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:56,000
He stole your girlfriend
and also sent someone to kill you too?

261
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:58,160
That's a bit much.

262
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:05,000
See? You think my world is beautiful,
luxurious, something to envy, right?

263
00:21:05,080 --> 00:21:07,920
But a life with no freedom,
where you're paranoid all the time,

264
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:10,720
is not romantic either.

265
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:14,320
Fine. Go ahead and take your little
field trip through poor people's life.

266
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:18,840
But I bet you won't last three days
before you run straight back home.

267
00:21:22,280 --> 00:21:25,480
- Bung! Bung!
- Huh?

268
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:27,040
Bung!

269
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,040
What's with you?

270
00:21:37,320 --> 00:21:39,040
Bung, are you okay?

271
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:41,600
Where does it hurt? Head? Shoulder? Butt?

272
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:43,440
- Did you get hurt?
- Hey.

273
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:46,280
- Huh?
- Hey, Kanah.

274
00:21:46,360 --> 00:21:47,360
Slow down.

275
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:49,840
- Huh?
- What's going on with you?

276
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:52,160
Didn't Mr. Song hurt you?

277
00:21:52,240 --> 00:21:54,520
Who told you that? Niuniu?

278
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:56,800
Or Samlee?

279
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:02,240
Niuniu first, then Samlee called again.

280
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:06,880
Come on. I'm the one who told them

281
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:10,520
to call me if anything happens.
Otherwise, you never tell me anything.

282
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:13,720
Your job is to study, so just study.

283
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:22,640
Bung, if I keep studying
only to make you suffer like this,

284
00:22:22,720 --> 00:22:24,160
then what am I studying for?

285
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:32,120
If you die right now,
who's going to pay my tuition? Right?

286
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:34,520
You little brat.

287
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:36,960
Hey, stop. Trai.

288
00:22:37,040 --> 00:22:39,600
- Trai, help. Stop.
- Stop.

289
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:40,680
Stop.

290
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:44,080
Hey, I'm wondering about something.

291
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:46,320
Why did Mr. Song come back
to mess with us again?

292
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:48,280
He disappeared for ages, didn't he?

293
00:22:55,840 --> 00:22:57,440
Oh, you were there too.

294
00:22:57,520 --> 00:22:58,720
I'll just ask Trai.

295
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:00,440
Mr. Song just missed us.

296
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:04,600
We didn't bring him
a New Year's gift basket.

297
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:08,040
See? You're always like this.

298
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:09,760
You never tell me anything!

299
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:12,520
Trai, tell me. You were there.

300
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:16,240
- Tell me. Come on, Trai.
- Kanah.

301
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:17,760
Are you sleeping at home tonight?

302
00:23:18,680 --> 00:23:19,960
Yeah.

303
00:23:20,840 --> 00:23:22,960
- What?
- Come. Right now.

304
00:23:23,040 --> 00:23:26,160
- Where are we going?
- What should we eat tomorrow?

305
00:23:26,760 --> 00:23:28,400
- See?
- What are we going to eat?

306
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:30,320
You never tell me anything, Bung.

307
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:36,440
- You don't tell me anything at all.
- This is already better than what I had.

308
00:23:37,160 --> 00:23:39,920
Come on, Trai.
Let's go. What are you waiting for?

309
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:41,800
- Yeah. I'm coming.
- Hurry or we won't make it.

310
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:43,520
Help me, Trai. Bung's hurting me.

311
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:46,600
- Trai, faster. Faster than that. Hurry.
- Alright, alright.

312
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:48,400
Bung. Hey, stop.

313
00:23:48,480 --> 00:23:50,440
- Trai, hurry up.
- Yeah, yeah.

314
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:10,040
So peaceful.

315
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:18,480
TO MR. TRAI
50 BAHT FOR CONGEE

316
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:21,760
30 BAHT FOR MINERAL WATER
FOR YOUR INFORMATION

317
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:25,480
Stingy.

318
00:24:41,120 --> 00:24:43,120
Pakbung!

319
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:45,000
Give my sister's money back.

320
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:50,520
Holy shit, Noy!

321
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:53,600
My sister's money! You're dead!

322
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:56,920
- Help me!
- Pakbung!

323
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,360
- Noy's going to kill me!
- Give me my sister's money!

324
00:24:59,440 --> 00:25:02,400
Pakbung!
Where do you think you're going? Move!

325
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:04,400
Get out of the way!

326
00:25:05,360 --> 00:25:07,000
Pakbung. Pakbung.

327
00:25:10,640 --> 00:25:13,880
Pakbung! Give me my sister's money!

328
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:28,040
- It's me.
- You?

329
00:25:30,640 --> 00:25:32,400
- How did you get here?
- I'd have to be deaf

330
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:33,720
to not hear that scream.

331
00:25:35,920 --> 00:25:36,840
And who's that?

332
00:25:37,440 --> 00:25:41,560
- He's Noy, Niuniu's little brother.
- The drug addict one?

333
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:44,560
Yeah. Fun, isn't it?

334
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:47,120
Let's go.

335
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:48,880
Hey! Pakbung!

336
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:52,960
You made my boss's ass hurt.
You have to pay for it.

337
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:56,760
Hey.

338
00:25:56,840 --> 00:25:57,920
Pakbung!

339
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:00,400
Where are you running to?

340
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:07,200
Pakbung, give me my sister's money.

341
00:26:08,160 --> 00:26:09,000
I'm not giving you anything.

342
00:26:10,160 --> 00:26:11,400
I'm not giving you anything either.

343
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:14,360
You don't get to choose.
You have to pay my boss's medical bills.

344
00:26:14,440 --> 00:26:15,600
I don't have it!

345
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:18,320
You do. How much do you have?

346
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:20,960
I don't. I'm not giving them.

347
00:26:21,040 --> 00:26:23,840
Hey! What are you doing?

348
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:26,120
Hey. Stop it.

349
00:26:27,800 --> 00:26:29,000
- What?
- This is all there is.

350
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:32,320
Every man for himself.
Split it among yourselves.

351
00:26:33,480 --> 00:26:35,200
Money!

352
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:38,600
Pakbung.

353
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:40,440
- Come on. Hurry.
- My money!

354
00:26:40,520 --> 00:26:42,280
- Hey!
- Dodge it.

355
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:46,160
- Hold him.
- My money!

356
00:26:47,080 --> 00:26:49,000
- He's on drugs.
- My money.

357
00:26:49,080 --> 00:26:50,560
My money.

358
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:52,600
- Come here.
- Let go of me!

359
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:54,000
Let go of me!

360
00:26:54,080 --> 00:26:56,120
- Let go of me.
- This way.

361
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:58,040
Over here! Officer.
It's my little brother.

362
00:26:58,120 --> 00:27:00,880
He assaulted Grandma. He's high right now.

363
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:03,160
- Officer, arrest him.
- Officer!

364
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:05,920
He's high! Let's go!

365
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:09,040
- Officer, get him out of here!
- Stop!

366
00:27:09,120 --> 00:27:11,240
- Stop! Stop!
- No!

367
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:18,200
- Arrest him, Officer. Grab his hands!
- Let go!

368
00:27:18,280 --> 00:27:19,600
There, there.

369
00:27:20,560 --> 00:27:21,640
Are you scared?

370
00:27:26,440 --> 00:27:27,560
Is this your normal life?

371
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:29,160
Not every day.

372
00:27:30,040 --> 00:27:31,440
Just once or twice a week.

373
00:27:32,680 --> 00:27:33,640
Those guys.

374
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:35,600
- Take him. Put him in jail.
- I'm not going!

375
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:38,480
They lock him up for a few days,
then he's out again.

376
00:27:42,760 --> 00:27:43,920
You can't handle it, right?

377
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:47,120
Then go home.

378
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:49,680
Go back to being rich, to your money,

379
00:27:49,760 --> 00:27:52,760
and come back later to pay me.

380
00:27:53,560 --> 00:27:54,400
No.

381
00:28:14,240 --> 00:28:15,680
Oh? Hey.

382
00:28:20,320 --> 00:28:22,120
So when am I getting my money?

383
00:28:23,520 --> 00:28:25,800
I just want to solve a problem
with money for once!

384
00:28:34,840 --> 00:28:35,720
Dr. Bee?

385
00:28:37,400 --> 00:28:39,920
Someone came looking
for the guy you brought here.

386
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:42,440
I remembered he had been beaten up,

387
00:28:42,520 --> 00:28:43,760
so I didn't dare say anything.

388
00:28:43,840 --> 00:28:45,640
How is he now?

389
00:28:46,520 --> 00:28:48,200
He's with me.

390
00:28:48,280 --> 00:28:50,800
Oh? So he didn't disappear anywhere.

391
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:52,960
Then why are they looking for him?

392
00:28:55,960 --> 00:28:57,400
Here, take this business card.

393
00:28:58,040 --> 00:29:00,800
That person is offering a reward
for anyone who reports a lead.

394
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:02,520
100,000.

395
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:05,360
Huh? 100,000?

396
00:29:06,880 --> 00:29:09,760
Report it and get paid right away?

397
00:29:09,840 --> 00:29:11,440
Hey, Pakbung.

398
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:12,600
Hurry!

399
00:29:12,680 --> 00:29:15,440
- Hurry, we've been waiting for you.
- Come.

400
00:29:18,160 --> 00:29:19,360
Hurry up.

401
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:21,120
- You go first.
- Is this cooked yet?

402
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:23,880
No money yet you guys
still want to eat BBQ?

403
00:29:24,520 --> 00:29:26,440
Mr. Trai's treating.

404
00:29:33,560 --> 00:29:34,680
Where'd you get any money from?

405
00:29:35,400 --> 00:29:36,440
I sold the watch,

406
00:29:37,520 --> 00:29:38,520
that fake watch.

407
00:29:39,480 --> 00:29:40,720
I got a few thousand for it.

408
00:29:42,600 --> 00:29:44,040
You should've paid me back.

409
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:50,080
Come on, living in the same house
means one wallet, right?

410
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:51,920
Just help each other earn, and also spend.

411
00:29:52,800 --> 00:29:55,160
But I'm not as good
at making money as Pakbung.

412
00:29:55,240 --> 00:29:57,360
How could she think about money
with every breath?

413
00:29:58,960 --> 00:30:01,720
Yeah, seriously.
You're only good at making money.

414
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:04,920
Why don't you try getting a man?

415
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:08,760
Kanah, so what should we do tonight?

416
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:12,880
Come sleep at my place.
Let's clear the way for them.

417
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:17,200
Trai, if you truly love my sister,

418
00:30:17,280 --> 00:30:19,040
I don't have a problem with that.

419
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:23,280
But can I get ten million as dowry?

420
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:28,600
Kanah, so you're not planning
to let your sister go at all?

421
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:30,400
Hey.

422
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:33,320
I've only got one sister.
I love her, and I'm protective.

423
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:36,400
If having a husband becomes
a burden, better not have one.

424
00:30:37,480 --> 00:30:38,840
Correct.

425
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:40,760
That's my brother.

426
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:46,920
Wow. Thank you!

427
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:49,720
Wait, wait.

428
00:30:49,800 --> 00:30:51,000
What if the husband is rich?

429
00:30:51,920 --> 00:30:53,080
- Yeah.
- Huh?

430
00:30:53,160 --> 00:30:54,000
That's your type, huh?

431
00:30:59,600 --> 00:31:02,840
Dating a man with money
doesn't mean he'll give me money.

432
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:07,080
I want money that's mine,
so I can spend it on whatever I want,

433
00:31:07,160 --> 00:31:09,400
no begging, no sweet-talking anyone.

434
00:31:12,280 --> 00:31:14,640
Confused, huh?

435
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:18,560
Listen, if you guys
want to buy stuff at 2 a.m.,

436
00:31:18,640 --> 00:31:21,800
between waking your husband up to transfer
or paying for yourself right then,

437
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:23,640
which would you choose?

438
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:24,640
- Transfer.
- Transfer.

439
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:31,800
Transfer by myself.

440
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:32,920
Yeah.

441
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:36,000
I wouldn't have to wake my husband.
I have money, so I'd transfer right away.

442
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:37,680
That's right.

443
00:31:38,520 --> 00:31:42,560
Unless your husband transfers
his entire bank account to you.

444
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:43,960
Then that's a different story.

445
00:31:45,920 --> 00:31:48,000
- Yeah.
- It was almost good.

446
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:51,360
When it comes to money,
I've gotta give it to you, Pakbung.

447
00:31:51,960 --> 00:31:54,400
Good thing I keep all my money with you,

448
00:31:55,040 --> 00:31:58,040
otherwise, Noy would've
taken everything by now.

449
00:32:00,200 --> 00:32:02,840
But I don't want too much freedom.

450
00:32:04,080 --> 00:32:06,160
I'm scared
I'll transfer it all to some guy.

451
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:10,040
That's why I told you
to keep your money with Pakbung.

452
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:12,000
Yeah. True.

453
00:32:17,440 --> 00:32:18,520
Trai…

454
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:22,360
What do you think?
My sister's cool, right?

455
00:32:23,280 --> 00:32:24,360
She loves money,

456
00:32:24,440 --> 00:32:26,760
but she's not selfish.

457
00:32:28,680 --> 00:32:29,960
Alright, come on.

458
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:36,240
Hoola… hoo!

459
00:32:39,480 --> 00:32:42,040
- Let's eat.
- Let's go!

460
00:32:44,320 --> 00:32:46,920
- Refill.
- The squid is all curly.

461
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:49,720
- Bacon?
- It's not cooked yet, Samlee.

462
00:32:49,800 --> 00:32:51,840
- Turn the heat up.
- Bacon.

463
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:53,440
- Trai, turn the heat up.
- Turn it up.

464
00:33:04,400 --> 00:33:06,240
Look…

465
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:08,920
So cute…

466
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:11,520
Aw…

467
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:14,760
Eat up. I'm taking you somewhere after.

468
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:21,320
Trai.

469
00:34:24,719 --> 00:34:27,840
Sorry, Da. The professor let us out late.

470
00:34:28,560 --> 00:34:29,400
It's okay.

471
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:37,040
Happy birthday, Trai.

472
00:34:44,040 --> 00:34:45,760
So you won't forget my face.

473
00:35:01,400 --> 00:35:03,920
I don't like anyone
meddling in my son's room.

474
00:35:11,560 --> 00:35:12,800
Don't you see?

475
00:35:13,880 --> 00:35:15,920
I've been in your son's room
this whole time.

476
00:35:17,480 --> 00:35:19,440
No matter where you look, it's me.

477
00:35:25,120 --> 00:35:26,440
And do you know

478
00:35:26,520 --> 00:35:29,280
why I don't throw all these photos away?

479
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:35,400
I'm going to wait for Trai to come back
and throw this trash away himself.

480
00:35:41,520 --> 00:35:43,600
And what if Trai refuses?

481
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:51,960
What if he keeps them
even closer than before?

482
00:35:54,920 --> 00:35:57,040
Do you really not know your son?

483
00:35:57,640 --> 00:35:58,840
Do you really not know

484
00:35:58,920 --> 00:36:01,000
how stubborn he is?

485
00:36:02,480 --> 00:36:04,160
No matter how stubborn he is,

486
00:36:05,640 --> 00:36:08,880
he won't be insane enough
to come take his father's wife.

487
00:36:09,760 --> 00:36:10,960
Right?

488
00:36:12,160 --> 00:36:14,920
Stop daydreaming, Darin.

489
00:36:18,440 --> 00:36:20,920
Have you ever truly loved anyone,
Mr. Tritot…

490
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:24,280
other than yourself?

491
00:36:46,760 --> 00:36:49,840
DUANGDAO KINDERGARTEN

492
00:36:49,920 --> 00:36:51,280
This is the place.

493
00:36:53,480 --> 00:36:57,880
I don't know why you brought me here, but…

494
00:36:58,680 --> 00:36:59,880
Oh?

495
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:03,720
Hey.

496
00:37:05,160 --> 00:37:08,080
That's trespassing, you know.

497
00:37:09,240 --> 00:37:10,760
Come on. Hurry.

498
00:37:16,960 --> 00:37:19,240
Hey… Hey.

499
00:37:19,920 --> 00:37:22,560
Hey, where did you go?

500
00:37:40,480 --> 00:37:43,320
Hey. Mr. Trai?

501
00:37:48,920 --> 00:37:52,400
Why are they howling now?

502
00:37:57,080 --> 00:37:57,960
Hey.

503
00:38:05,400 --> 00:38:06,280
Hey.

504
00:38:07,960 --> 00:38:08,920
Hey.

505
00:38:10,840 --> 00:38:13,440
Mr. Trai. Where are you?

506
00:38:20,640 --> 00:38:21,560
It's me.

507
00:38:22,600 --> 00:38:23,840
Follow me.

508
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:26,000
Hey.

509
00:38:27,200 --> 00:38:30,320
Schools at night are already creepy.

510
00:38:31,120 --> 00:38:32,480
This one's abandoned too.

511
00:38:32,560 --> 00:38:35,120
Why didn't we come during the day?

512
00:38:38,640 --> 00:38:39,720
Scared?

513
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:43,880
Of course I'm not scared.
I'm about to pee myself.

514
00:38:48,360 --> 00:38:50,800
Don't be loud. The ghosts might hear you.

515
00:38:51,840 --> 00:38:54,040
What ghosts? This is my mom's old school.

516
00:38:56,240 --> 00:38:57,240
- Your mom's?
- Yeah.

517
00:38:58,480 --> 00:39:00,760
My mom was a teacher
and the owner of this school.

518
00:39:02,280 --> 00:39:05,000
But after she passed away,
no one took care of it anymore.

519
00:39:06,720 --> 00:39:08,040
I'm sorry,

520
00:39:09,560 --> 00:39:12,720
but your mom didn't die here, right?

521
00:39:16,840 --> 00:39:20,080
And no kids died here either, did they?

522
00:39:22,120 --> 00:39:23,320
You wanna meet them?

523
00:39:33,640 --> 00:39:34,640
Hey.

524
00:39:37,280 --> 00:39:39,960
Well, you're scared too.

525
00:39:41,200 --> 00:39:43,200
What? I was just startled by your scream.

526
00:39:45,920 --> 00:39:47,920
- Come on.
- Hey. Wait.

527
00:39:51,800 --> 00:39:52,640
Take me with you.

528
00:39:55,720 --> 00:39:56,720
Alright, come on.

529
00:40:19,040 --> 00:40:21,400
I want to renovate this place.

530
00:40:21,480 --> 00:40:23,440
I plan to reopen the school.

531
00:40:24,760 --> 00:40:27,280
And where are you going to get the money?

532
00:40:28,520 --> 00:40:30,880
Do you see these things?

533
00:40:31,600 --> 00:40:33,680
They're antiques,
from my grandfather's time.

534
00:40:34,640 --> 00:40:37,400
They're all worth money. I'll sell them.

535
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:41,640
And I'll mortgage the land with the bank
and take out a loan to build it.

536
00:40:44,960 --> 00:40:46,560
I understand now

537
00:40:47,720 --> 00:40:50,320
why you and your dad
have so many problems.

538
00:40:51,360 --> 00:40:53,640
From being a billionaire heir

539
00:40:54,680 --> 00:40:56,760
to wanting to open
a small school like this?

540
00:40:57,920 --> 00:40:59,240
You're thinking the same as my dad?

541
00:41:00,120 --> 00:41:01,600
That I can't do it?

542
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:04,160
No.

543
00:41:05,240 --> 00:41:07,720
I'm just jealous of you for having a dream

544
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:10,720
and trying to fight for it.

545
00:41:11,560 --> 00:41:13,840
The world I live in runs on money.

546
00:41:13,920 --> 00:41:16,520
Every dream costs money.

547
00:41:17,840 --> 00:41:20,280
I'm too tired
to reach for something beyond myself.

548
00:41:22,400 --> 00:41:26,280
Someone like me doesn't have dreams.

549
00:41:31,440 --> 00:41:33,000
Then do you wanna share a dream with me?

550
00:41:35,120 --> 00:41:37,760
This area's an old neighborhood.
Many tourists pass through here.

551
00:41:38,440 --> 00:41:41,520
If we set up shops outside,
they could generate some income.

552
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:43,800
Be my partner.

553
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:46,360
No need to invest money, just work.

554
00:41:46,960 --> 00:41:49,600
We might not get rich,

555
00:41:49,680 --> 00:41:51,040
but you'll never go hungry.

556
00:42:10,800 --> 00:42:12,280
First, we'll need to vacuum.

557
00:42:13,920 --> 00:42:17,240
This is not good. It's all dust.
Maybe call a housekeeper?

558
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:38,360
Wow.

559
00:42:39,040 --> 00:42:40,400
I really miss my mom.

560
00:42:42,160 --> 00:42:44,360
When I was a kid,
I used to come play with her here.

561
00:42:48,480 --> 00:42:52,600
<i>Hold on tight, okay?</i>
<i>You're about to fly, Trai!</i>

562
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:56,400
You want me to push harder?

563
00:42:56,480 --> 00:42:57,520
Yes!

564
00:42:57,600 --> 00:43:00,400
If you want it higher,
you have to say you love me really loud.

565
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:02,560
I love you, Mom!

566
00:43:02,640 --> 00:43:05,120
Now I've got the strength.

567
00:43:05,720 --> 00:43:08,280
Alright, here we go!

568
00:43:29,720 --> 00:43:32,040
When I was a kid, I used to go
to the playground with my mom too.

569
00:43:34,280 --> 00:43:35,920
My mom was a tour guide.

570
00:43:37,040 --> 00:43:38,960
Sometimes, she took me with her.

571
00:43:39,640 --> 00:43:41,160
But the day she fell off the boat,

572
00:43:42,320 --> 00:43:43,280
I wasn't there.

573
00:43:47,720 --> 00:43:49,480
Looks like the two of us…

574
00:43:50,520 --> 00:43:52,480
both lost our moms.

575
00:43:56,560 --> 00:43:58,800
And we both have problems
with our dads too.

576
00:44:04,840 --> 00:44:06,960
My dad was an investor

577
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:10,040
but the kind who invested in gambling.

578
00:44:12,160 --> 00:44:15,040
After my mom died, he ran out of money.

579
00:44:16,040 --> 00:44:19,200
So he borrowed from Mr. Song.
The more he borrowed,

580
00:44:19,280 --> 00:44:20,960
the worse it got.

581
00:44:21,040 --> 00:44:23,200
When he couldn't pay it back, he ran away

582
00:44:23,280 --> 00:44:26,240
without telling me anything.

583
00:44:26,320 --> 00:44:27,840
I was about 15 then.

584
00:44:31,000 --> 00:44:32,760
You and Kanah were really young then.

585
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:35,120
Yes.

586
00:44:35,800 --> 00:44:37,360
I was totally lost.

587
00:44:37,440 --> 00:44:39,880
But what could I do?
I had to pull myself together.

588
00:44:41,200 --> 00:44:43,480
So I applied for scholarships

589
00:44:43,560 --> 00:44:45,720
and studied and worked at the same time.

590
00:44:46,560 --> 00:44:48,960
Wow. That's impressive.

591
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:51,240
I think so too.

592
00:44:57,800 --> 00:44:58,760
As for me,

593
00:44:59,600 --> 00:45:00,840
after my mom died,

594
00:45:01,680 --> 00:45:03,480
my dad became obsessed
with work and money.

595
00:45:04,760 --> 00:45:06,280
He raised me like an asset.

596
00:45:07,040 --> 00:45:09,160
All he cared about
was utility and maximizing profits.

597
00:45:11,320 --> 00:45:13,120
We never ate together,

598
00:45:14,440 --> 00:45:16,080
never laughed together,

599
00:45:17,560 --> 00:45:19,080
couldn't even speak nicely to each other.

600
00:45:23,360 --> 00:45:25,680
I struggle physically.

601
00:45:26,720 --> 00:45:29,480
You struggle emotionally.

602
00:45:31,400 --> 00:45:33,280
We're not competing over trauma, right?

603
00:45:35,720 --> 00:45:37,200
Either way,

604
00:45:37,280 --> 00:45:38,920
I win.

605
00:45:40,600 --> 00:45:41,880
- Hey, Pakbung. Hey.
- Oh?

606
00:45:46,200 --> 00:45:48,080
- You okay?
- Ow, why…

607
00:45:49,040 --> 00:45:50,560
Why did it just fall apart?!

608
00:45:51,240 --> 00:45:54,200
I was about to say it was old.
I was too late.

609
00:45:59,560 --> 00:46:01,800
Why does life never go my way?!

610
00:46:05,040 --> 00:46:06,520
But what can I do?

611
00:46:07,360 --> 00:46:08,960
I just have to keep fighting.

612
00:46:09,880 --> 00:46:11,360
Keep fighting, girl!

613
00:46:26,840 --> 00:46:27,680
Thank you.

614
00:46:30,680 --> 00:46:31,840
For what?

615
00:46:55,480 --> 00:46:57,920
Have you ever truly loved anyone,
Mr. Tritot…

616
00:46:59,760 --> 00:47:01,360
other than yourself?

617
00:47:03,360 --> 00:47:04,680
Why wouldn't I have?

618
00:47:21,360 --> 00:47:22,960
My mom's name was Duangdao.

619
00:47:24,720 --> 00:47:26,040
Whenever I feel lonely,

620
00:47:26,800 --> 00:47:28,560
I talk to her like this.

621
00:47:31,440 --> 00:47:32,400
Mom,

622
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:34,760
I'm about to start a new life.

623
00:47:35,480 --> 00:47:37,240
And I want to make our dream come true.

624
00:47:44,400 --> 00:47:45,680
Try it.

625
00:47:53,120 --> 00:47:55,880
Mom, I'm really tired.

626
00:47:56,720 --> 00:47:59,760
Next draw, can I win the lottery jackpot,
six digits straight?

627
00:48:01,160 --> 00:48:02,640
Can you be serious for once?

628
00:48:05,440 --> 00:48:07,000
I'm being serious here.

629
00:48:08,480 --> 00:48:10,640
But I don't want my mom to see me.

630
00:48:12,160 --> 00:48:14,680
If she's gone,
I want her to really be gone.

631
00:48:14,760 --> 00:48:17,040
No worries, no burdens.

632
00:48:39,400 --> 00:48:40,440
Here.

633
00:48:42,680 --> 00:48:43,800
A good kid reward.

634
00:48:44,680 --> 00:48:45,560
No.

635
00:48:54,600 --> 00:48:57,200
Mom used to put star stickers on kids
when they behaved well.

636
00:48:58,600 --> 00:49:00,400
I found them in a drawer inside.

637
00:49:04,960 --> 00:49:06,120
You're a good person, Pakbung.

638
00:49:07,680 --> 00:49:08,720
Even if you're stingy,

639
00:49:09,640 --> 00:49:11,560
money-hungry, or obsessed

640
00:49:12,400 --> 00:49:13,480
with money sometimes…

641
00:49:17,800 --> 00:49:19,320
you're sincere.

642
00:49:20,800 --> 00:49:22,480
Not like the people I've met before.

643
00:49:28,640 --> 00:49:30,240
Alright.

644
00:49:33,880 --> 00:49:35,600
Let's be friends, Pakbung.

645
00:49:52,400 --> 00:49:53,720
Hoo…

646
00:49:59,280 --> 00:50:01,040
- Hool…
- Hoola…

647
00:50:03,200 --> 00:50:05,400
- Hoola…
- Hoola…

648
00:50:05,480 --> 00:50:06,440
Hoo!

649
00:50:10,840 --> 00:50:11,880
Who came up with that move?

650
00:50:11,960 --> 00:50:13,200
We did together.

651
00:50:14,280 --> 00:50:15,760
Are you bullying me?

652
00:50:33,400 --> 00:50:36,520
<i>That person is offering a reward</i>
<i>for anyone who reports a lead.</i>

653
00:50:36,600 --> 00:50:37,440
<i>100,000.</i>

654
00:50:53,120 --> 00:50:55,080
TRAI

655
00:51:20,520 --> 00:51:22,280
Tonight's party

656
00:51:22,880 --> 00:51:25,080
is the most important job of my life.

657
00:51:25,680 --> 00:51:28,040
Do you know how hard it was

658
00:51:28,120 --> 00:51:30,000
for me to get this job?

659
00:51:30,600 --> 00:51:34,440
So please, I'm begging you.

660
00:51:34,520 --> 00:51:38,000
Do your best. Don't let anything go wrong.

661
00:51:38,080 --> 00:51:42,120
I repeat. Do not let anything go wrong.

662
00:51:44,200 --> 00:51:45,000
- Yes!
- Yes!

663
00:52:06,960 --> 00:52:07,920
Ready?

664
00:52:08,960 --> 00:52:11,640
Work tirelessly, get paid fully,

665
00:52:11,720 --> 00:52:15,520
make customers happy. Yay!

666
00:52:18,440 --> 00:52:21,120
What are you standing around for? Go work.

667
00:52:21,760 --> 00:52:23,160
- Yes!
- Yes!

668
00:52:37,680 --> 00:52:39,120
Is it done yet?

669
00:52:41,840 --> 00:52:42,760
Thank you.

670
00:52:51,360 --> 00:52:52,560
Are you okay?

671
00:52:53,080 --> 00:52:54,280
I'm fine. Don't worry.

672
00:52:55,840 --> 00:52:57,520
100 for each clear glass.

673
00:52:58,440 --> 00:52:59,960
500 for each wine glass.

674
00:53:01,280 --> 00:53:02,600
Break one and you pay.

675
00:53:04,400 --> 00:53:05,680
Stingy.

676
00:53:09,040 --> 00:53:11,560
Hello. Hello, everyone.

677
00:53:11,640 --> 00:53:14,320
And the moment you've all
been waiting for is finally here.

678
00:53:14,400 --> 00:53:18,560
Please welcome
Mrs. Mookmanee and Ms. Mika!

679
00:53:39,160 --> 00:53:40,520
- Hello.
- Dad?

680
00:53:40,600 --> 00:53:42,360
- Happy birthday, Mika.
- Thank you.

681
00:53:42,440 --> 00:53:43,400
Wishing you lots of happiness.

682
00:53:44,520 --> 00:53:45,840
What a lovely party.

683
00:53:56,280 --> 00:53:57,520
Excuse me for a moment.

684
00:54:07,760 --> 00:54:10,200
- Dad. Dad.
- Yeah?

685
00:54:11,120 --> 00:54:13,280
You didn't tell me
you were coming to this party.

686
00:54:13,880 --> 00:54:16,720
Well, I've been doing business
with Mrs. Mookmanee for ages.

687
00:54:16,800 --> 00:54:18,120
Why wouldn't I come?

688
00:54:36,240 --> 00:54:38,960
Mr. Trai, I saw your dad.

689
00:54:41,000 --> 00:54:42,280
He came with your ex.

690
00:54:42,800 --> 00:54:44,200
My brother's here too.

691
00:54:46,200 --> 00:54:47,760
Is this some kind of reunion party?

692
00:54:50,280 --> 00:54:51,760
I just remembered.

693
00:54:51,840 --> 00:54:54,960
Mrs. Mookmanee owns a bank
and is also my dad's new business partner.

694
00:54:55,040 --> 00:54:56,120
It was big news for a while.

695
00:54:56,720 --> 00:54:59,080
So what now? You wanna leave first?

696
00:55:01,000 --> 00:55:01,920
I…

697
00:55:04,080 --> 00:55:05,200
Or…

698
00:55:06,360 --> 00:55:07,560
do you wanna talk to your ex?

699
00:55:08,520 --> 00:55:11,320
Why would I?
Things ended the moment she chose my dad.

700
00:55:11,400 --> 00:55:12,640
Then do you wanna curse her out?

701
00:55:14,200 --> 00:55:15,680
You're gonna let her be happy

702
00:55:15,760 --> 00:55:18,040
while you stand on the bridge suffering?

703
00:55:18,120 --> 00:55:19,320
That's not fair.

704
00:55:19,400 --> 00:55:22,240
At the very least,
go over there and poke her a little.

705
00:55:22,320 --> 00:55:23,560
Make her flinch.

706
00:55:25,200 --> 00:55:27,080
You're in? I'll help.

707
00:55:27,160 --> 00:55:29,960
Why are you acting weird today?
How much do you want?

708
00:55:31,280 --> 00:55:34,000
Free. For a friend.

709
00:55:38,520 --> 00:55:39,360
Pakbung.

710
00:55:47,560 --> 00:55:49,440
Leave us for now.

711
00:56:00,120 --> 00:56:03,080
Ms. Kaew did find irregularities
in the minority shareholders, sir.

712
00:56:03,160 --> 00:56:05,280
We're investigating the details
to confirm everything.

713
00:56:09,520 --> 00:56:11,920
Be Rich shares
are attractive in the market.

714
00:56:13,800 --> 00:56:16,640
People who already hold them
might want more.

715
00:56:16,720 --> 00:56:18,400
- Don't let anyone know.
- Yes, sir.

716
00:56:25,520 --> 00:56:26,360
What is it?

717
00:56:27,080 --> 00:56:30,360
Mr. Tritot suspects certain executives

718
00:56:30,440 --> 00:56:32,880
are quietly buying up shares
from minority shareholders.

719
00:56:32,960 --> 00:56:35,800
This is the one behind Be Rich's success.

720
00:56:36,400 --> 00:56:38,640
He’s the reason I decided to buy shares.

721
00:56:39,920 --> 00:56:41,840
You're giving me far too much credit,
Mrs. Mookmanee.

722
00:56:42,760 --> 00:56:44,880
- It's true.
- Thank you.

723
00:56:59,440 --> 00:57:02,600
"Someone wants to see you."
"Front entrance."

724
00:57:06,320 --> 00:57:09,360
Hey, have you seen Mr. Tritot's new wife?

725
00:57:09,440 --> 00:57:11,160
She's pretty decent looking.

726
00:57:11,240 --> 00:57:13,840
Oh, please, of course she is.

727
00:57:13,920 --> 00:57:16,280
She's a Grade-A escort, you know.

728
00:57:16,360 --> 00:57:20,240
Oh, my! Mr. Tritot actually went
and married that kind of woman?

729
00:57:20,920 --> 00:57:22,240
So cheap.

730
00:57:22,320 --> 00:57:24,240
Rich man, pretty woman,

731
00:57:24,320 --> 00:57:26,400
- that’s just the way it goes.
- Hey.

732
00:57:29,360 --> 00:57:30,280
Let's go.

733
00:57:31,640 --> 00:57:32,560
Excuse me.

734
00:57:39,960 --> 00:57:40,920
An escort?

735
00:57:49,360 --> 00:57:51,080
<i>You ruined my daughter's birthday party.</i>

736
00:57:51,160 --> 00:57:52,120
I won't let this slide.

737
00:57:54,240 --> 00:57:56,960
- How dare you ruin Ms. Mika's birthday.
- Dad?

738
00:57:58,040 --> 00:57:59,240
<i>Mr. Trai.</i>

739
00:57:59,840 --> 00:58:00,920
Then just die already!

740
00:58:01,000 --> 00:58:02,680
So Dad will only have me!

741
00:58:02,760 --> 00:58:04,640
Do it then. Kill me!

742
00:58:04,720 --> 00:58:06,160
Kill me!

743
00:58:06,240 --> 00:58:08,920
They're suing us
for 20 million in damages.

744
00:58:09,000 --> 00:58:10,160
20 million?

745
00:58:10,240 --> 00:58:13,000
People like you have ruined
so many bosses already, you know.

746
00:58:13,960 --> 00:58:15,200
You dare challenge my mother?

747
00:58:15,280 --> 00:58:16,680
<i>I'll use the media to take them down.</i>

748
00:58:18,560 --> 00:58:21,360
<i>From now on,</i>
<i>there will only be friendship.</i>

749
00:58:21,440 --> 00:58:23,800
<i>Heart for heart. Nothing owed.</i>

750
00:58:23,880 --> 00:58:24,960
You're still just as funny.

751
00:58:25,040 --> 00:58:26,520
What do you want?

752
00:58:26,600 --> 00:58:28,280
You really don't recognize me?

753
00:58:30,400 --> 00:58:31,480
Have you found him?

754
00:59:24,240 --> 00:59:26,720
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
